              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The He-6 secondary beam was produced by the",
                "fragmentation of a 75 MeV/nucleon primary C-13 beam on",
                "carbon production target located between the two",
                "superconducting solenoids of the SISSI  device. The",
                "intensity of the He-6 secondary beam on the reaction",
                "target in the SPEG  area was of the order of 10E+5 pps",
                "at a energy of 38.3 MeV/nucleon."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The scattered particles were identified in th",
                "focal plane of the SPEG spectrometer (see Nucl.Instr.",
                "Meth.A276,509-520,1989)",
                "The energy  resolution of the SPEG spectrometer",
                " (delta-E/E=10E-3) allows the measurement of the",
                "elastic scattering data of light nuclei with complete",
                "separation of inelastic scattering from target",
                "excitations."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A position-sensitive microchannel plate was",
                "placed in front of the target and provided the stop",
                "signal for the beam detectors.",
                "plastic scintillator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Optical model."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.All calculated cross sections for the",
